 The Vosman Police have now issued a media statement, urging community members to assist them with the search. Motubatse was arrested on 23 March 2018, for murder, after his employer, Ms Alta Maree was reported as missing in February. After investigations, Motubatse pointed out a shallow grave to the police, where human remains were found.
The remains were sent for DNA testing to confirm whether they indeed belong to Ms Maree. While the DNA results have not yet been released, Ms Maree’s family are convinced that she was murdered. The Vosman Police are urging members of the community to assist in the location of their suspect. Anyone with information on his whereabouts can contact Sergeant Constance Beryl Prinsloo at 084 589 1128 or the Vosman Police Station at 013 659 8400.    Parents frustrated by a lack of space in Middelburg schools Traffic officers to appear in court for corruption #TrafficAlert: Two dead in Kranspoort accidents VIDEO: Two perish after truck jack-knifes • Save our standby number (072 248 3855) and send us a WhatsApp message with the words “Add me” to be added to our broadcast list. • Like us on Facebook, follow us on Twitter and Instagram. • Subscribe to our YouTube channel. • Click on the link to subscribe to our bi-weekly newsletter via email. Contact our news room on our 24 hr standby number 072 248 3855, or send a mail to our editor tobie@mobserver.co.za